Description: Handle sliver of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay near fine light brown.
Curator's comments: Name Polyaratos. The condition of the piece suggests it is from Naukratis. Trimmed. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR 024.32.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1131)
